rComments: I am graduating soon but I still think professor Mackay is simply the BEST professor in the entire MIE department. We need more professors like him to teach students.
Very accessible outside of class, helpful in emails and in office hours, uses his own handouts for all examinable materials. The course is lecture-heavy so dont miss his classes. Great prof
He is very knowledgeable and very nice! The course is very well organized.

Absolutely amazing. Cool and engaging prof who puts so much effortt into helping us learn. I honestly had hated circuits before this class, but the clear lectures, the notes, and the demos made it surprisingly fun.
AWESOME PROF. Helps outside of class, excellent lectures, fair marking. Clearly cares about students.

Hand down the best professor in MIE. Most professors are academically gifted but have no idea how to teach. Professor Mackay knows how to teach and engage with his students, especially tackling pressing problems with a constructed approach. Very helpful in his office hours too!

Professor Mackay is simply one of the best professors in Mechanical Engineering at the University of Toronto. He is always there for his students and is very helpful. His lectures are very valuable and interesting . I highly recommend taking a class with professor Mackay.
